result.name: Eiffel Bistro

reviews.text:
Nice and relaxed bistro. Nice and polite servers

We went during brunch/lunch time (around 1300?) lunch set comes with starters, main and dessert plus a drink (tea or coffee). Starter was nice and small and mains were good size too. The hanger steak was absolutely best

I saw the brunch toast at the table next to us and definitely need to come again
Average food but comfortable seats. Friendly waitresses, reasonable set lunches.

They have this cheap trick with the drinks; the beers are llisted on the menu as 500ml, then cone in 400ml glasses. They’re quite aware of the deception. Just note, happy hour is not as happy as expected!
Pretty cosy bistro. Food is OK, perhaps not rustic enough as myb only criticism
Excellent lunch set deal with delicious hanger steak!
